        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 2:50AM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 249 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near New Carlisle to Walkerton. Movement was
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
South Bend, Mishawaka, Niles, Buchanan, Gulivoire Park, Granger,
Walkerton, North Liberty, New Carlisle, Lakeville, Roseland,
Bertrand, Dayton, Indian Village, Chain-o-lakes, Crumstown, Woodland,
Lydick, and Wyatt.

This includes Interstate 80 in Indiana between mile markers 62 and
79.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
